LAGOS – As part of activities lined up to celebrate Pastor Adeboye’s 80th birthday, His Love Foundation (HLF), the charity arm of RCCG will extend its medical intervention programme to the people of Abuja and Bauchi with the commissioning of Enoch and Folu Adeboye Dialysis Centre at Wuse District Hospital on 17th February 2022 and at Abubakar Tafawa Balewa Teaching Hospital, Bauchi on 19th February 2022, bringing the number of dialysis machines commissioned across Nigeria to 37. In the two centres, there will be a total of 11 dialysis machines, two medical mater reverse osmosis purification systems and two dedicated 30KVA generators.In a statement according to the HLF, the centres sited in Abuja and Bauchi are specifically to ensure that the impact of the projects of the charity organisation continues to spread across the length and breadth of the country. The statement said the foundation has donated the Enoch and Folu Adeboye Intensive Care Units in four hospitals namely Lagos State University Teaching Hospital (LASUTH), Plateau State Specialist Hospital, Plateau State, Redeemers Health Centre, Mowe Ogun State, and Ondo State School Of Medical Sciences Teaching Hospital, Ondo State ICU. 2022: God Has Something Special For Bayelsa – Pastor… Pastor Adeboye, Bishop Wale Oke, PFN, Others For YMR Retreat The foundation has also donated The Enoch and Folu Adeboye Dialysis Units in seven hospitals aside the one to be commissioned in Abuja and Bauchi. They are the Healing Stripes Dialysis Center, Oniru, Victoria Island, Lagos State; Olabisi Onabanjo Teaching Hospital, Shagamu Ogun State, Redeemers Health Care Centre, Ibadan, Oyo State; Ondo State School of Medical Sciences Teaching Hospital, Ondo State;University College Hospital, Ibadan, Oyo State; Gbagada General Hospital, Lagos State. The foundation has also has set up a cancer screening centre called Healing Stripes Cancer Screening Centre, Lagos State; two X-ray units at Ondo State School of Medical Sciences Teaching Hospital, Ondo State; and Redeemers Health Centre Mowe, Ogun State; one Cardiac Diagnostic Unit at Ondo State School of Medical Sciences Teaching Hospital, Ondo State. His Love Foundation through its health initiatives has impacted about nine million lives and has spent over N25 billion in the last three years on various social interventions. The commissioning event will be attended by eminent persons in government and within the Redeemed Christian Church of God leadership.